How Vaping Can Put You in Hospital #novape While vaping has been touted as a safer alternative to smoking traditional cigarettes, it is not without its risks. Inhaling the aerosol produced by e-cigarettes can expose your lungs to a variety of harmful substances, including: Nicotine: Nicotine is a highly addictive substance that can harm the developing brain in young people. It can also increase the risk of heart disease, stroke, and lung cancer. Nicotine liquid in a vape pen Opens in a new window  www.buyv2cigs.co.uk Nicotine liquid in a vape pen Ultrafine particles: These tiny particles can be inhaled deep into the lungs and may increase the risk of lung disease. Flavorings: Some flavorings used in e-cigarettes have been linked to lung disease. Volatile organic compounds (VOCs): VOCs are harmful chemicals that can irritate the lungs and eyes. Heavy metals: Some e-cigarettes contain trace amounts of heavy metals, such as lead and nickel, which can be harmful to the nervous system.  In addition to these long-term health risks, vaping can also cause immediate side effects, such as: Coughing: Vaping can irritate the lining of the lungs and cause a cough. Shortness of breath: Vaping can make it difficult to breathe. Chest pain: Vaping can cause chest pain. Nausea and vomiting: Vaping can cause nausea and vomiting.  If you are considering vaping, it is important to be aware of the potential risks. Replying to @donnamarie34 The Truth About Perimenopause.  Are you going through unexpected physical changes during midlife?  If so, perimenopause may be one of the reason behind it.  Perimenopause is the transitional stage before menopause, marking the end of your reproductive years.  For most women, it begins around 40 to 44 years old, but it varies among individuals.  As your hormones change, your periods eventually stop, and after 12 missed cycles, your perimenopause period is over.  Some common signs of perimenopause: hot flashes, night sweats, mood changes, decreased libido, sleep difficulties, vaginal dryness, joint and muscle aches, and headaches. Have you ever experienced any of these?  You don't need to suffer. You can still feel relief and manage these perimenopausal symptoms during your midlife. #perimenopause #perimenopausesymptoms #perimenopausehealth #hotflashes #nightsweat #moodswings #libido #sleep#jointpain #musclepain #headache #womenover40 #womenshealth

What is it that Causes Your Eye to Twitch? #myokymia  Myokymia is a neuromuscular condition characterized by involuntary and spontaneous muscle twitching or quivering, typically in small, localized areas of the body. These twitches are often described as rippling or worm-like movements and can occur in muscles around the eyes, face, limbs, or other parts of the body. The exact cause of myokymia is not fully understood, but it is believed to be related to abnormalities in the nerve cells that control muscle contraction. Factors such as stress, fatigue, caffeine, excessive use of digital screens, and electrolyte imbalances may contribute to the occurrence or exacerbation of myokymia. While myokymia is generally harmless and self-limiting, it can be bothersome and concerning to those experiencing it. In most cases, the twitches resolve spontaneously without any specific treatment. However, managing stress levels, getting adequate rest, and avoiding triggers such as excessive caffeine intake or eye strain may help reduce the frequency or intensity of myokymic episodes. If myokymia becomes persistent, widespread, or is accompanied by other symptoms, it is advisable to seek medical attention. Rarely, myokymia can be a sign of an underlying neurological disorder or nerve dysfunction that requires further evaluation and treatment. Understanding myokymia as a benign condition can provide reassurance to individuals experiencing these muscle twitches, but it's always important to consult with a healthcare professional for proper diagnosis and guidance. #Myokymia #MuscleTwitching #NeuromuscularCondition #InvoluntaryMovements #SpontaneousTwitches #MuscleQuivering #NeurologicalDisorder #NerveDysfunction #StressManagement #Fatigue #CaffeineSensitivity #DigitalEyeStrain #ElectrolyteImbalance #SelfLimitingCondition #Neurology #MuscleSpasms #BenignMuscleTwitches #HealthAwareness #MedicalAttention #SeekAdvice #doctor #medicine #healthcare #interesting #interestingfacts #interestingvideos #interestingthings #healthcare #eyetwitch #eyetwitching
